comments: O'Neale (BKN) lifts his pivot foot prior to releasing his dribble.
Siakam (TOR) establishes himself in Bridges' (BKN) path and marginal contact occurs as the defensive switch occurs.
Finney-Smith (BKN) cleanly deflects the ball away from Barnes (TOR) during rebounding.
Siakam (TOR) brings his forearm towards Bridges' (BKN) front and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Siakam (TOR) moves alongside Bridges' (BKN) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Finney-Smith (BKN) and Schroder (TOR) come together at the same spot and Schroder spins off of the marginal contact.
Dinwiddie (BKN) contests Trent Jr.'s (TOR) shot and marginal contact occurs after the release.
Barnes (TOR) avoids making contact with Dinwiddie's (BKN) arm, and Dinwiddie loses control of his dribble on his own.
Barnes (TOR) and Bridges (BKN) come together at the same spot and marginal lower body contact occurs as Johnson (BKN) elevates for the shot.

As Bridges (BKN) removes his left hand from the ball, his forearm makes some contact with Barnes' (TOR) head/neck area.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Bridges (BKN) brings his hands towards Barnes' (TOR) front, and he absorbs the marginal contact during the shot attempt.
Barnes (TOR) commits a take foul on Johnson (BKN).
Finney-Smith (BKN) raises his hand to pursue the rebound, and marginal contact occurs with Barnes (TOR) during rebounding.
Anunoby (TOR) legally contests Finney-Smith's (BKN) jump shot attempt.
Barnes (TOR) commits a take foul on Dinwiddie (BKN).
Bridges (BKN) legally contests Anunoby's (TOR) jump shot attempt.
